To Italy now, where both Corriere dello Sport and La Gazzetta Sportiva lead with Roma's 2-2 draw with Sassuolo in which the Giallorossi salvaged a point thanks to two goals fro Serbian Adem Ljajic.

'Without six first choice players, Roma catch Sassuolo with two goals from the Serbian,' write Corriere dello Sport.

While La Gazzetta Sportiva also hail 10 man Roma for showing 'heart' to come from behind despite Daniele de Rossi's red card.  

